## Plan Mode Optimization Rules

### Rule CTX-007: Execute Prompts Must Produce the Standard Execution Plan in Plan Mode

Every **execute prompt** (Type B: 01-B, 01-C, 01-E, 01-F; and Type C: 03, 04, 05) must produce the standard Execution Plan format in Plan mode before creating any file. The standard format is defined in `.cursor/templates/context/EXECUTION-PLAN-TEMPLATE.md`.

The Execution Plan must always include all of the following sections:
- **Context Loaded**: what was read from context files or disk, with one-sentence summaries
- **Scope**: file count and estimated execution duration
- **File Manifest**: every file to be created with path, template, and content outline
- **Key Decisions**: decisions that will be made during execution with preliminary conclusions
- **Assumptions**: any gaps in inputs and what assumption covers them
- **Execution Order**: files/tasks ordered by dependency with reasoning

Producing a simple file path list without these sections violates this rule.

```
# Correct Plan mode behavior:
1. Read all required context files and docs
2. Produce the full Execution Plan (standard format)
3. Present it to the user
4. Wait for confirmation (CTX-009)
5. Execute only after confirmation

# Incorrect Plan mode behavior:
1. List file paths only
2. Say "confirm to proceed"
→ Violates CTX-007: missing File Manifest content outlines, Key Decisions, Assumptions
```

### Rule CTX-008: File Manifest Must Include Content Outlines

The **File Manifest** table in the Execution Plan must include a content outline column for every file. A content outline is 1–2 sentences describing:
- What the key sections of the file will contain
- What specific decisions or information will be embedded
- What templates will be used

A manifest entry that contains only a file path and template name, with no content outline, is incomplete and violates this rule.

```markdown
# Correct File Manifest entry:
| 1 | docs/architecture/domains/identity/ARCHITECTURE.md | _DOMAIN-TEMPLATE.md | Will define User, Role, Session entities; document OAuth2 flow from Vision Section 8; include ERD and two sequence diagrams for login and token refresh |

# Incorrect File Manifest entry:
| 1 | docs/architecture/domains/identity/ARCHITECTURE.md | _DOMAIN-TEMPLATE.md | Domain architecture document |
→ Violates CTX-008: no content outline
```

### Rule CTX-009: Mandatory Confirmation Gate Before Execution

No file may be created by an execute prompt until the user has explicitly confirmed the Execution Plan. The confirmation gate is the final line of the Execution Plan:

> **Ready to execute. Confirm to switch to Agent mode.**

After presenting the Execution Plan:
- **Wait** for the user to confirm
- If the user requests changes, update the plan and re-present
- Only after explicit confirmation: switch to execution and begin creating files
- **Never** begin file creation in the same turn as the Execution Plan presentation

This rule is the enforcement mechanism for the Plan → Execute workflow. Violating it defeats the purpose of Plan mode.

